# PostgreSQL SQL Dialect

Use PostgreSQL dialect exclusively. Do NOT use Snowflake, T-SQL, or Spark SQL syntax.

## PostgreSQL-Specific Features
- JSONB for semi-structured data (not JSON, not VARIANT)
- LATERAL for row expansion
- ON CONFLICT for upserts (INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE)
- RETURNING clause for getting affected rows
- `::type` or CAST(x AS type) for casting
- COALESCE(), NULLIF() for null handling
- CASE WHEN for conditionals (NOT IFF())
- Window functions with subquery for filtering (no QUALIFY)

## Do NOT Use
- IFF() (Snowflake-only)
- QUALIFY (Snowflake-only)
- VARIANT (Snowflake-only)
- LATERAL FLATTEN (Snowflake-only)
- explode() (Spark SQL-only)
- MERGE INTO (prefer ON CONFLICT for PostgreSQL)
- TRY_CAST (Snowflake-only, not standard PostgreSQL)

## Date/Time Functions
- NOW(), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_DATE
- date_trunc('month', column), date_part('year', column)
- column + INTERVAL '1 day'
- AGE(timestamp1, timestamp2)
- EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM interval)

## String Functions
- string_agg(), array_agg()
- LEFT(), RIGHT(), SUBSTRING()
- REGEXP_MATCHES(), REGEXP_REPLACE()
